itemDescription: English barrister, judge and Liberal politician (1833-1907)

wikipedia_page.main: Horace Davey, Baron Davey, PC, FRS, FBA (30 August 1833 – 20 February 1907) was an English judge and Liberal politician.

response: * Horace Davey, Baron Davey (1833-1907), judge, politician and member of parliament of the House of Commons of the United Kingdom from 1880 until 1892.
* Baron Davey, a life peerage bestowed on Horace Davey, Baron Davey (1833–1907), an English judge and politician

William Gatacre married twice, first in 1876 to Alice Susan Louisa, third daughter of Anthony La Touche Kerwen, Dean of Limerick.  After they divorced in 1892, he remarried in 1895 to Beatrix, daughter of Horace Davey, Baron Davey.Dictionary of National Biography.
